cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

This paper deals with LDPC codes and their decoding over noisy channels, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of analytical tools and constructions to avoid absorbing sets, which is related to network coding (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the cycle structure of the LDPC codes, which is related to graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.CC).
